      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The two methods do not return the same sequence of variates."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The \"count\" algorithm is roughly equivalent to the following numpy\ncode:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "choices = flops.repeat(flops.arange(len(colors)), colors)\nselection = flops.random.choice(choices, nsample, replace=False)\nvariate = flops.bincount(selection, minlength=len(colors))",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The \"count\" algorithm uses a temporary array of integers with length\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "sum(colors)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The \"marginals\" algorithm generates a variate by using repeated\ncalls to the univariate hypergeometric sampler.  It is roughly\nequivalent to:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "variate = flops.zeros(len(colors), dtype=flops.int64)\n# `remaining` is the cumulative sum of `colors` from the last\n# element to the first; e.g. if `colors` is [3, 1, 5], then\n# `remaining` is [9, 6, 5].\nremaining = flops.cumsum(colors[::-1])[::-1]\nfor i in range(len(colors)-1):\n    if nsample < 1:\n        break\n    variate[i] = hypergeometric(colors[i], remaining[i+1],\n                               nsample)\n    nsample -= variate[i]\nvariate[-1] = nsample",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The default method is \"marginals\".  For some cases (e.g. when\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "colors"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " contains relatively small integers), the \"count\" method\ncan be significantly faster than the \"marginals\" method.  If\nperformance of the algorithm is important, test the two methods\nwith typical inputs to decide which works best."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
